Class ObjectTable<T>

java.lang.Object
au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.collections.tables.TableAdapter
au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.collections.tables.ObjectTable<T>
Type Parameters:
T - Any Object descendant except primitive wrappers; for String, use StringTable
All Implemented Interfaces:
Table, fr.ens.biologie.generic.DataContainer, fr.ens.biologie.generic.SaveableAsText, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Showable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sizeable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Textable, Cloneable
public class ObjectTable<T> extends TableAdapter

A multidimensional generic Table to contain any Object descendant.

By construct, the implementation of contentType() at this level cannot return better than the Object class. To return the exact T class, a descendant of ObjectTable where T is explicited must be written.

Similarly, the usual static valueOf() method cannot be implemented here, only in descendant classes.

Author:
Shayne Flint - looong ago
  • modified by JG 15/2/2017 to account for Table and DataContainer interfaces
  • modified by JG 1/10/2018 to account for Textable interface
  • modified by JG 3/2/2021 to fix the valueOf(...) issues
